A weathered knight in mismatched armor riding a tired horse across a vast Spanish plain at golden hour, tilting his lance toward a massive wooden windmill that towers against a dramatic amber sky. The knight's posture is defiant and noble despite his ragged appearance, his tattered cape billowing behind him. In the distance, more windmills dot the rolling hills of La Mancha. The scene is rendered in rich, warm vintage tones reminiscent of 19th-century romantic oil paintings, with visible brushstroke textures and a slightly faded, aged quality like an illustration from an antique book. The composition emphasizes the small figure against the enormous windmill, capturing both the absurdity and the profound dignity of charging against impossible odds.
